column42:
In my opinion, AI works best as a tool rather than a solution to everything. Always use it as a source of inspiration rather than a full replacement of human work. This is true for text-based generation like GPT, but also visual generation like Stable Diffusion.

AI seems to know what people like, as it should because that data is what it is trained on. However, design is in large part about innovation. AI brings true and tested results, which are not always desired.
column305: I firmly believe that AI like GPT is best used as a source of inspiration for many aspects in game design, including narrative. However, it can never be used as a reliable source nor can you expect the quality of the output to be entirely useful without edits.

column315: As I am currently design lead on a Branching Narrative project, I have seen the tools used in some capacity. Tools like ChatGPT often give out relatively standard solutions to problems in our Narrative. These solutions can be helpful and give an overview of what can be achieved. However, there is still a great deal of human work required for these branches to be interesting and engaging. By specifying a bit more regarding what output you are hoping to receive from the AI model, it can go a bit more advanced, granting better outlines to work with.
